== Installation ==
1. Copy the folder "SOOP_RSS_MATLAB_CODE" or checkout the last subversion byt typing in you shell :
   'rm -rf [ProgramLocationDestination];   svn export  https://svn.emii.org.au/repos/SOOP_CURRENT_JOB/trunk/ [ProgramLocationDestination]
2. Open config.txt to change the location of :
-script.path :location of the scripts (from the checkout)
-python.path :location of the python binary
-matlab.path :location of the matlab binary
-df.path	 :location of the datafabric(or cloud storage)
-dataSOOP.path:location of the SOOP scripts output (log + data)
-logFile.name:name of the log file
-email1.log	 :email to send to the first user (for each current job)
-email2.log  :email to send to the second user (for each current job) - NOT REQUIRED
3. Create a link of SOOP.sh to /usr/bin/ by executing in you shell 
sudo ln -s /[ProgramLocation]/SOOP.sh /usr/local/bin/SOOP_AIMS_Download
4. install the python module  from http://pypi.python.org/pypi/configobj/ . 1 wget *zip, unzip *.zip, python setup.py install
5. Execute the program by typing in your shell 'SOOP_AIMS_Download'


== System Requirements ==
Internet connection
Tested with MATLAB R2010a

Operating System Support
The following operating systems are supported under V2.0:
Ubuntu 9.10 (cat /etc/issue to check your version)

To find and download an earlier version that might supports other operating systems, refer to:
https://svn.emii.org.au/repos/SOOP_aims_CURRENT_JOB/trunk/


